title: Varshini emerges champion
text:
Varshini emerges champion Varshini emerges champion October 11, 2015,Bengaluru, DHNS 
Varshini V of Tamil Nadu emerged champion with a round to spare in the girls section of the 26th National Open and girls under-17 chess championships here on Saturday. Varshini overcame Aditee Prabhgaonkar of Goa in the 10th round to take her tally to an unassailable 9.5 points.Meanwhile in the Open section, West Bengalâ€™s Rajdeep Sarkar and Vaishali R of Tamil Nadu shared the top spot with eight points each at the end of 10th round. Results (top 10): Open: WFM Vaishali R (TN, 8 points) drew with Krishna Teja N (AP, 7); FM Rajdeep Sarkar (WB, 8) drew with Dhananjay (Chha, 7); Muthaiah Al (TN, 7) bt Pranavananda V (AP, 7); Barath Kalyan M (TN, 6) lt to Kumaran B (TN, 7); Erigaisi Arjun (Tel, 6) lt to Karthik V (AP, 7); Athul Krishna S (Ker, 6) lt to Shailesh Dravid (Mah, 7); Harikrishnan A (TN, 7) bt Jayakumaar S (TN, 6); Sai Vishwesh C (TN, 6) drew with Dhanush Bharadwaj (Kar, 6); Adhithya S (TN, 6) drew with Vaisnav M (TN, 6); Rajarishi Karthi (TN, 6) drew with Rahul Srivatshav P (Tel, 6).Girls: Prabhugaonkar Aditee Aman (Goa, 6.5) lt to WFM Varshini V (TN, 9.5); Toshali V (AP, 7.5) bt Vantika Agrawal (Del, 7); WFM Mahalakshmi M (TN, 7.5) bt WFM Potluri Supreetha (AP, 6); Divya Lakshmi R (TN, 7) drew with Smaraki Mohanty (Odi, 6.5); Thamaraiselvi P (TN, 6.5) bt WFM Bidhar Rutumbara (Odi, 5.5); Potluri Saye Srreezza (Tel, 6) drew with Senthamizh Yazhini S (TN, 6); WCM Swera Ana Braganca (Goa, 5.5) lt to Shah Vishwa (Mah, 6.5); Kavitha PL (TN, 6) drew with Abirama Srinithi G (TN, 6); WCM Isha Sharma (Kar, 6.5) bt Jadhav Vaibhavi (Mah, 5.5); Sreelakshmi M Sunilkumar (Ker, 5.5) lt to Varsha CR (TN, 6.5).
